Thank you for your aid with Greyhoof Meadows. The high quality of the centaurs' armaments makes it difficult for us to retain control of the meadows. Finding the source—likely bandit suppliers—will be critical to pushing them out of these lands once and for all. 

Regardless, distributing badges to the families of fallen Seraph is of the utmost importance to us, and you have helped make that possible. Now we can finally give those families something to commemorate their loved ones' service. 

—Sergeant Rane

Greetings traveller,

The resource-laden forests and hills of the Iron Marches are quite dangerous. It was bad enough after the Searing of Ascalon decimated the entire region. Now the dragon brand draws a near impassable line between Lion's Arch and the far east. We are most pleased to learn that explorers such as yourself are still making their way into the territory.

Keep up the good work.

— Tyrian Explorers Society
